    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/libreoffice-core--9c8b85f3", "path": "include/sfx2/app.hxx", "symbol": "SfxApplication"}
  ],
  "text": "The LibreOffice document model architecture is built on a hierarchy of document classes, with SfxObjectShell serving as the foundational base class. Here are the key files and classes that define the core document framework:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx, line 182): The base document shell class that all document types inherit from. It is defined as `class SFX2_DLLPUBLIC SfxObjectShell : public SfxShell, public SotObject`. This class manages the document lifecycle, persistence, and integration with the LibreOffice framework.\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx, line 196): The Writer (word processor) document class, defined as `class SwDoc final`. This represents the model of a Writer document and contains all the document-specific data for text processing.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx, line 331): The Calc (spreadsheet) document class, defined as `class ScDocument`. This is the central data structure for spreadsheet documents, managing all sheets, cells, and data.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx, line 338): The Impress/Draw document class, defined as `class SD_DLLPUBLIC SdDrawDocument final : public FmFormModel`. This manages presentation and drawing documents, including pages, shapes, and animations.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx, line 103): The LibreOffice application framework entry point, defined as `class SFX2_DLLPUBLIC SfxApplication final : public SfxShell`. This is the singleton application object that manages the overall LibreOffice framework, including windows, documents, modules, and global state.\n\nAll document-specific classes (SwDoc, ScDocument, SdDrawDocument) ultimately inherit from or work with SfxObjectShell, which provides the document shell abstraction. The SfxApplication class manages these documents at the application level, coordinating between the framework and individual document implementations."
}

